11#ifndef MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_DECODING_STATE_H_
12#define MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_DECODING_STATE_H_
13
14#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
15#include <cstdint>
16#endif
17
18#include <map>
19#include <set>
20#include <vector>
21
22namespace webrtc {
23
24// Forward declarations
25struct NaluInfo;
26class VCMFrameBuffer;
27class VCMPacket;
28
29class VCMDecodingState {
30 public:
31 // The max number of bits used to reference back
32 // to a previous frame when using flexible mode.
33 static const uint16_t kNumRefBits = 7;
34 static const uint16_t kFrameDecodedLength = 1 << kNumRefBits;
35
36 VCMDecodingState();
37 ~VCMDecodingState();
38 // Check for old frame
39 bool IsOldFrame(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame) const;
40 // Check for old packet
41 bool IsOldPacket(const VCMPacket* packet) const;
42 // Check for frame continuity based on current decoded state. Use best method
43 // possible, i.e. temporal info, picture ID or sequence number.
44 bool ContinuousFrame(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame) const;
45 void SetState(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame);
46 void CopyFrom(const VCMDecodingState& state);
47 bool UpdateEmptyFrame(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame);
48 // Update the sequence number if the timestamp matches current state and the
49 // sequence number is higher than the current one. This accounts for packets
50 // arriving late.
51 void UpdateOldPacket(const VCMPacket* packet);
52 void SetSeqNum(uint16_t new_seq_num);
53 void Reset();
54 uint32_t time_stamp() const;
55 uint16_t sequence_num() const;
56 // Return true if at initial state.
57 bool in_initial_state() const;
58 // Return true when sync is on - decode all layers.
59 bool full_sync() const;
60
61 private:
62 void UpdateSyncState(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame);
63 // Designated continuity functions
64 bool ContinuousPictureId(int picture_id) const;
65 bool ContinuousSeqNum(uint16_t seq_num) const;
66 bool ContinuousLayer(int temporal_id, int tl0_pic_id) const;
67 bool ContinuousFrameRefs(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame) const;
68 bool UsingPictureId(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame) const;
69 bool UsingFlexibleMode(const VCMFrameBuffer* frame) const;
70 bool AheadOfFramesDecodedClearedTo(uint16_t index) const;
71 bool HaveSpsAndPps(const std::vector<NaluInfo>& nalus) const;
72
73 // Keep state of last decoded frame.
74 // TODO(mikhal/stefan): create designated classes to handle these types.
75 uint16_t sequence_num_;
76 uint32_t time_stamp_;
77 int picture_id_;
78 int temporal_id_;
79 int tl0_pic_id_;
80 bool full_sync_; // Sync flag when temporal layers are used.
81 bool in_initial_state_;
82
83 // Used to check references in flexible mode.
84 bool frame_decoded_[kFrameDecodedLength];
85 uint16_t frame_decoded_cleared_to_;
86 std::set<int> received_sps_;
87 std::map<int, int> received_pps_;
88};
89
90} // namespace webrtc
91
92#endif // MODULES_VIDEO_CODING_DECODING_STATE_H_
